metadata.name: THE MISFIT #1/30
metadata.description:
The Misfit

Hold on!!! Hear Me Out!!!  
I'm pushed out of the group because I'm perceived as different. 
I'm labelled a misfit because I'm unusual and "something" might be wrong with me.  
You call me a black sheep because I'm not the usual.  
The jokes on you though.  
Because I'm not scared to be my weird unique self.  
I'm strong because even when talked about, I continue in my path.  
I've embraced my uniqueness and I'm loving this weirdness.  
Yes I'm a misfit, but I didn't chose to be.  
 I'm just it and I'm not sorry.
